#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2850
#, no-wrap
msgid "@option{sshx} method with cygwin"
msgstr "@option{sshx} method with cygwin"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2856
msgid ""
"Cygwin's @command{ssh} works only with a Cygwin version of Emacs.  To check "
"for compatibility: type @kbd{M-x eshell @key{RET}}, and start @kbd{ssh test."
"host @key{RET}}.  Incompatibilities trigger this message:"
msgstr ""
"Cygwin の @command{ssh} は、Emacs の Cygwin バージョンでのみ機能します。 互換"
"性を確認するには、 @kbd{M-x eshell @key{RET}} と入力し、 @kbd{ssh test.host "
"@key{RET}} を開始します。 非互換性により、 以下のメッセージがトリガーされま"
"す:"

#. type: example
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2859
#, no-wrap
msgid "Pseudo-terminal will not be allocated because stdin is not a terminal.\n"
msgstr "Pseudo-terminal will not be allocated because stdin is not a terminal.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2864
msgid ""
"Some older versions of Cygwin's @command{ssh} work with the @option{sshx} "
"access method.  Consult Cygwin's FAQ at @uref{https://cygwin.com/faq/} for "
"details."
msgstr ""
"Cygwin の @command{ssh} の一部の古いバージョンは、 @option{sshx} アクセス方式"
"で動作します。 詳細については、 @uref{https://cygwin.com/faq/} で Cygwin の "
"FAQ を参照してください。"

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2865
#, no-wrap
msgid "cygwin and @command{fakecygpty}"
msgstr "cygwin and @command{fakecygpty}"

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2866
#, no-wrap
msgid "@command{fakecygpty} and cygwin"
msgstr "@command{fakecygpty} and cygwin"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2871
msgid ""
"On @uref{https://www.emacswiki.org/emacs/SshWithNTEmacs, the Emacs Wiki} it "
"is explained how to use the helper program @command{fakecygpty} to fix this "
"problem."
msgstr ""
"@uref{https://www.emacswiki.org/emacs/SshWithNTEmacs, the Emacs Wiki} では、 "
"ヘルパー・プログラム @command{fakecygpty} を使用してこの問題を修正する方法が"
"説明されています。"

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2872
#, no-wrap
msgid "method @option{scpx} with cygwin"
msgstr "method @option{scpx} with cygwin"

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2873
#, no-wrap
msgid "@option{scpx} method with cygwin"
msgstr "@option{scpx} method with cygwin"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2880
msgid ""
"When using the @option{scpx} access method, Emacs may call @command{scp} "
"with MS Windows file naming, such as @file{c:/foo}.  But the version of "
"@command{scp} that is installed with Cygwin does not know about MS Windows "
"file naming, which causes it to incorrectly look for a host named @samp{c}."
msgstr ""
"@option{scpx} アクセス方式を使用する場合、 Emacs は、 @file{c:/foo} などの "
"MS Windows ファイル名で @command{scp} を呼び出すことができます。 しかし、 "
"Cygwin とともにインストールされた @command{scp} のバージョンは、 MS Windows "
"のファイル命名法を認識しないため、 @samp{c} という名前のホストを誤って検索し"
"ます。"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2883
msgid ""
"A workaround: write a wrapper script for @option{scp} to convert Windows "
"file names to Cygwin file names."
msgstr ""
"回避策(workaround): @option{scp} のラッパー・スクリプトを記述して、 Windows "
"ファイル名を Cygwin ファイル名に変換します。"

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2884
#, no-wrap
msgid "cygwin and @command{ssh-agent}"
msgstr "cygwin and @command{ssh-agent}"

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2885
#, no-wrap
msgid "@env{SSH_AUTH_SOCK} and emacs on ms windows"
msgstr "@env{SSH_AUTH_SOCK} and emacs on ms windows"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2886
#, no-wrap
msgid "SSH_AUTH_SOCK@r{, environment variable}"
msgstr "SSH_AUTH_SOCK@r{, environment variable}"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2892
msgid ""
"When using the @command{ssh-agent} on MS Windows for password-less "
"interaction, @option{ssh} methods depend on the environment variable "
"@env{SSH_AUTH_SOCK}.  But this variable is not set when Emacs is started "
"from a Desktop shortcut and authentication fails."
msgstr ""
"MS Windows でパスワードなしの対話に @command{ssh-agent} を使用する場合、 "
"@option{ssh} 方式は環境変数 @env{SSH_AUTH_SOCK} に依存します。 ただし、 "
"Emacs がデスクトップ・ショートカットから起動され、 かつ、 認証が失敗した場"
"合、 この変数は設定されません。"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2895
msgid ""
"One workaround is to use an MS Windows based SSH Agent, such as "
"@command{Pageant}.  It is part of the PuTTY Suite of tools."
msgstr ""
"回避策の１つは、 @command{Pageant} などの MS Windows ベースの SSH エージェン"
"トを使用することです。 これは PuTTY スイートの一部です。"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2897
msgid "The fallback is to start Emacs from a shell."
msgstr "最後の手段は、 シェルから Emacs を起動することです。"

#. type: section
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2900
#, no-wrap
msgid "@acronym{FUSE} setup hints"
msgstr "@acronym{FUSE} setup hints"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2907
msgid ""
"The @acronym{FUSE} file systems are mounted by default at @file{/tmp/tramp."
"method.user@@host#port}.  The user name and port number are optional.  If "
"the file system is already mounted, it will be used as it is.  If the mount "
"point does not exist yet, @value{tramp} creates this directory."
msgstr ""
"@acronym{FUSE} ファイル・システムは、 デフォルトで @file{/tmp/tramp.method."
"user@@host#port} にマウントされます。 ユーザー名とポート番号はオプションで"
"す。 ファイル・システムがすでにマウントされている場合は、 そのまま使用されま"
"す。 マウント・ポイントがまだ存在しない場合、 @value{tramp} はこのディレクト"
"リを作成します。"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2911
msgid ""
"The mount point can be overwritten by the connection property @t{\"mount-"
"point\"}, @ref{Predefined connection information}.  Example:"
msgstr ""
"マウント・ポイントは、 接続プロパティ @t{\"mount-point\"} によって上書きでき"
"ます(@ref{Predefined connection information})。 例:"

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2918
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(add-to-list 'tramp-connection-properties\n"
"             `(,(regexp-quote \"@trampfn{sshfs,user@@host,}\")\n"
"               \"mount-point\"\n"
"               ,(expand-file-name \"sshfs.user@@host\" user-emacs-directory)))\n"
msgstr ""
"(add-to-list 'tramp-connection-properties\n"
"             `(,(regexp-quote \"@trampfn{sshfs,user@@host,}\")\n"
"               \"mount-point\"\n"
"               ,(expand-file-name \"sshfs.user@@host\" user-emacs-directory)))\n"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2921
#, no-wrap
msgid "tramp-fuse-unmount-on-cleanup"
msgstr "tramp-fuse-unmount-on-cleanup"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2925
msgid ""
"The user option @code{tramp-fuse-unmount-on-cleanup}, when set to non-"
"@code{nil}, controls, whether a mount point is unmounted on connection "
"cleanup or on Emacs exiting."
msgstr ""
"ユーザー・オプション @code{tramp-fuse-unmount-on-cleanup} が 非 @code{nil} 設"
"定されている場合、 接続のクリーンアップ時または Emacs の終了時にマウント・ポ"
"イントがアンマウントされるかどうかを制御します。"

#. type: anchor{#1}
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2928
msgid "Setup of rclone method"
msgstr "Setup of rclone method"

#. type: subsection
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2928
#, no-wrap
msgid "@option{rclone} setup"
msgstr "@option{rclone} setup"

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2929
#, no-wrap
msgid "rclone setup"
msgstr "rclone setup"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2935
msgid ""
"The default arguments of the @command{rclone} operations @command{mount}, "
"@command{coopyto}, @command{moveto} and @command{about} are declared in the "
"variable @code{tramp-methods} as method specific parameters.  Usually, they "
"don't need to be overwritten."
msgstr ""
"@command{rclone} の @command{mount} 操作や @command{coopyto} 操作や "
"@command{moveto} 操作や @command{about} 操作のデフォルト引数は、方式(method)"
"固有のパラメータとして変数 @code{tramp-methods} で宣言されます。 通常、上書き"
"する必要はありません。"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2940
msgid ""
"If needed, these parameters can be overwritten as connection properties "
"@t{\"mount-args\"}, @t{\"copyto-args\"}, @t{\"moveto-args\"} and @t{\"about-"
"args\"}, @xref{Predefined connection information}.  All of them are list of "
"strings."
msgstr ""
"必要に応じて、 これらのパラメーターは、 接続プロパティ @t{\"mount-args\"} や "
"@t{\"copyto-args\"} や @t{\"moveto-args\"} や @t{\"about-args\"} として上書き"
"できます(@xref{Predefined connection information})。 これらはすべて文字列のリ"
"ストです。"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2943
msgid ""
"Be careful changing @t{\"--dir-cache-time\"}, this could delay visibility of "
"files."
msgstr ""
"@t{\"--dir-cache-time\"} の変更には注意してください。 これにより、ファイルの"
"表示が遅くなる可能性があります。"

#. type: anchor{#1}
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2946
msgid "Setup of sshfs method"
msgstr "Setup of sshfs method"

#. type: subsection
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2946
#, no-wrap
msgid "@option{sshfs} setup"
msgstr "@option{sshfs} setup"

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2947
#, no-wrap
msgid "sshfs setup"
msgstr "sshfs setup"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2953
msgid ""
"The method @option{sshfs} declares the mount arguments in the variable "
"@code{tramp-methods}, passed to the @command{sshfs} command.  This is a list "
"of list of strings, and can be overwritten by the connection property "
"@t{\"mount-args\"}, @xref{Predefined connection information}."
msgstr ""
"@option{sshfs} 方式は、 @command{sshfs} コマンドに渡される変数 @code{tramp-"
"methods} でマウント引数を宣言します。 これは文字列のリストのリストであり、 接"
"続プロパティ @t{\"mount-args\"} によって上書きできます(@xref{Predefined "
"connection information})。"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2957
msgid ""
"Additionally, it declares also the arguments for running remote processes, "
"using the @command{ssh} command.  These don't need to be changed."
msgstr ""
"さらに、 @command{ssh} コマンドを使用して、 リモート・プロセスを実行するため"
"の引数も宣言します。 これらは変更する必要はありません。"

#. type: section
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2960
#, no-wrap
msgid "Android shell setup hints"
msgstr "Android shell setup hints"

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2961
#, no-wrap
msgid "android shell setup for ssh"
msgstr "android shell setup for ssh"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2969
msgid ""
"@value{tramp} uses the @option{adb} method to access Android devices.  "
"Android devices provide a restricted shell access through an USB "
"connection.  The local host must have the @command{adb} program installed.  "
"Usually, it is sufficient to open the file @file{@trampfn{adb,,/}}.  Then "
"you can navigate in the file system via @code{dired}."
msgstr ""
"@value{tramp} は @option{adb} 方式(method)を使用して Android デバイスにアクセ"
"スします。 Android デバイスは、 USB 接続を介して制限付きシェル・アクセスを提"
"供します。 ローカル・ホストには @command{adb} プログラムがインストールされて"
"いる必要があります。 通常、 ファイル @file{@trampfn{adb,,/}} を開くだけで十分"
"です。 その後、 @code{dired} を介してファイル・システムをナビゲートできます。"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2973
msgid ""
"Alternatively, applications such as @code{Termux} or @code{SSHDroid} that "
"run @command{sshd} process on the Android device can accept any @option{ssh}-"
"based methods provided these settings are adjusted:"
msgstr ""
"あるいは、 Android デバイスで @command{sshd} プロセスを実行する "
"@code{Termux} や @code{SSHDroid} などのアプリケーションは、 これらの設定が調"
"整されていれば、 @option{ssh} ベースの方式(method)を受け入れることができます:"

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2979
msgid ""
"@command{sh} must be specified for remote shell since Android devices do not "
"provide @command{/bin/sh}.  @command{sh} will then invoke whatever shell is "
"installed on the device with this setting:"
msgstr ""
"Android デバイスは @command{/bin/sh} を提供しないため、 リモート・シェルには "
"@command{sh} を指定する必要があります。 @command{sh} は、 以下の設定でデバイ"
"スにインストールされているシェルを呼び出します:"

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2984
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(add-to-list 'tramp-connection-properties\n"
"             (list (regexp-quote \"192.168.0.26\") \"remote-shell\" \"sh\"))\n"
msgstr ""
"(add-to-list 'tramp-connection-properties\n"
"             (list (regexp-quote \"192.168.0.26\") \"remote-shell\" \"sh\"))\n"

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2990
msgid ""
"where @samp{192.168.0.26} is the Android device's IP address.  "
"(@pxref{Predefined connection information})."
msgstr ""
"ここで、 @samp{192.168.0.26} は Android デバイスの IP アドレスです。 "
"(@pxref{Predefined connection information})。"

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2997
msgid ""
"On the Android device the directory names are prefixed with an application "
"specific prefix, which is @file{/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/bin} instead "
"of @file{/usr/bin} in the @code{Termux} case.  You must adapt the file names "
"in @code{tramp-remote-path}, for example via connection-local settings"
msgstr ""
"Android デバイスでは、 ディレクトリ名の前にアプリケーション固有のプレフィック"
"スが付きます。 これは、 @code{Termux} の場合、 @file{/usr/bin} ではなく、 "
"@file{/data/data/com.termux/files/usr/bin} です。 @code{tramp-remote-path} で"
"ファイル名を調整する必要があります。 @code{tramp-remote-path} のファイル名"
"を、 たとえば以下のように connection-local 設定を介して調整する必要があります"

#. type: ifinfo
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:2999
msgid "(@pxref{Connection Variables, , , emacs}):"
msgstr "(@pxref{Connection Variables, , , emacs})"

#. type: ifnotinfo
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3002
msgid ":"
msgstr ":"

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3013
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(connection-local-set-profile-variables\n"
" 'tramp-connection-local-termux-profile\n"
" `((tramp-remote-path\n"
"    . ,(mapcar\n"
"\t(lambda (x)\n"
"\t  (if (stringp x) (concat \"/data/data/com.termux/files\" x) x))\n"
"\t(copy-tree tramp-remote-path)))))\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"(connection-local-set-profile-variables\n"
" 'tramp-connection-local-termux-profile\n"
" `((tramp-remote-path\n"
"    . ,(mapcar\n"
"\t(lambda (x)\n"
"\t  (if (stringp x) (concat \"/data/data/com.termux/files\" x) x))\n"
"\t(copy-tree tramp-remote-path)))))\n"
"\n"

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3017
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(connection-local-set-profiles\n"
" '(:application tramp :machine \"192.168.0.26\")\n"
" 'tramp-connection-local-termux-profile)\n"
msgstr ""
"(connection-local-set-profiles\n"
" '(:application tramp :machine \"192.168.0.26\")\n"
" 'tramp-connection-local-termux-profile)\n"

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3023
msgid ""
"When the Android device is not @samp{rooted}, specify a writable directory "
"for temporary files:"
msgstr "Android デバイスがルート化(@samp{rooted})されてない場合は、 一時ファイル用に書き込み可能なディレクトリを指定します:"

#. type: lisp
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3028
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(add-to-list 'tramp-connection-properties\n"
"             (list (regexp-quote \"192.168.0.26\")\n"
"\t\t   \"tmpdir\" \"/data/data/com.termux/files/home/tmp\"))\n"
msgstr ""
"(add-to-list 'tramp-connection-properties\n"
"             (list (regexp-quote \"192.168.0.26\")\n"
"\t\t   \"tmpdir\" \"/data/data/com.termux/files/home/tmp\"))\n"

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3034
msgid ""
"Open a remote connection with the command @kbd{C-x C-f "
"@trampfn{ssh,192.168.0.26#2222,} @key{RET}}, where @command{sshd} is "
"listening on port @samp{2222}."
msgstr "コマンド @kbd{C-x C-f @trampfn{ssh,192.168.0.26#2222,} @key{RET}} でリモート接続を開きます。 ここで、 @command{sshd} はポート @samp{2222} でリッスンしています。"

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3037
msgid ""
"To add a corresponding entry to the @file{~/.ssh/config} file (recommended), "
"use this:"
msgstr "(推奨)対応するエントリを @file{~/.ssh/config} ファイルに追加するには、 以下を使用します:"

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3044
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Host android\n"
"     HostName 192.168.0.26\n"
"     User root\n"
"     Port 2222\n"
msgstr ""
"Host android\n"
"     HostName 192.168.0.26\n"
"     User root\n"
"     Port 2222\n"

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3050
msgid ""
"To use the host name @samp{android} instead of the IP address shown in the "
"previous example, fix the connection properties as follows:"
msgstr "上記例で示した IP アドレスの代わりにホスト名 @samp{android} を使用するには、 接続プロパティを以下のように修正します:"

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3061
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(add-to-list 'tramp-connection-properties\n"
"             (list (regexp-quote \"android\") \"remote-shell\" \"sh\"))\n"
"(add-to-list 'tramp-connection-properties\n"
"             (list (regexp-quote \"android\")\n"
"\t\t   \"tmpdir\" \"/data/data/com.termux/files/home/tmp\"))\n"
"(connection-local-set-profiles\n"
" '(:application tramp :machine \"android\")\n"
" 'tramp-connection-local-termux-profile)\n"
msgstr ""
"(add-to-list 'tramp-connection-properties\n"
"             (list (regexp-quote \"android\") \"remote-shell\" \"sh\"))\n"
"(add-to-list 'tramp-connection-properties\n"
"             (list (regexp-quote \"android\")\n"
"\t\t   \"tmpdir\" \"/data/data/com.termux/files/home/tmp\"))\n"
"(connection-local-set-profiles\n"
" '(:application tramp :machine \"android\")\n"
" 'tramp-connection-local-termux-profile)\n"

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3067
msgid ""
"Open a remote connection with the more concise command @kbd{C-x C-f "
"@trampfn{ssh,android,} @key{RET}}."
msgstr "これにより、 より簡潔なコマンド @kbd{C-x C-f @trampfn{ssh,android,} @key{RET}} でリモート接続を開けます。"

#. type: section
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3071
#, no-wrap
msgid "Auto-save, File Lock and Backup configuration"
msgstr "Auto-save, File Lock and Backup configuration"

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3072
#, no-wrap
msgid "auto-save"
msgstr "auto-save"

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3073
#, no-wrap
msgid "file-lock"
msgstr "file-lock"

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3074
#, no-wrap
msgid "backup"
msgstr "backup"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3076
#, no-wrap
msgid "backup-directory-alist"
msgstr "backup-directory-alist"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3080
msgid ""
"To avoid @value{tramp} from saving backup files owned by @samp{root} to "
"locations accessible to others, default backup settings in @code{backup-"
"directory-alist} have to be altered."
msgstr "@value{tramp} が、 @samp{root} が所有するバックアップ・ファイルを他のユーザーがアクセスできる場所に保存することを回避するには、 @code{backup-directory-alist} のデフォルトのバックアップ設定を変更する必要があります。"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3089
msgid ""
"Here's a scenario where files could be inadvertently exposed.  Emacs by "
"default writes backup files to the same directory as the original files "
"unless changed to another location, such as @file{~/.emacs.d/backups/}.  "
"Such a directory will also be used by default by @value{tramp} when using, "
"say, a restricted file @file{@trampfn{su,root@@localhost,/etc/secretfile}}.  "
"The backup file of the secretfile is now owned by the user logged in from "
"@value{tramp} and not @samp{root}."
msgstr "ファイルが誤って公開される可能性があるシナリオを以下に示します。 デフォルトでは、 @file{~/.emacs.d/backups/} などの別の場所に変更されない限り、 Emacs は元のファイルと同じディレクトリにバックアップ・ファイルを書き込みます。 このようなディレクトリは、 たとえば、制限付きファイル @file{@trampfn{su,root@@localhost,/etc/secretfile}} を使用する場合、 @value{tramp} によってデフォルトで使用されます。 secretfile のバックアップ・ファイルは、 @samp{root} ではなく、 @value{tramp} からログインしたユーザーが所有するようになりました。"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3092
msgid ""
"When @code{backup-directory-alist} is @code{nil} (the default), such "
"problems do not occur."
msgstr "@code{backup-directory-alist} が @code{nil} (デフォルト) の場合、 このような問題は発生しません。"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3095
msgid ""
"To ``turn off'' the backup feature for remote files and stop @value{tramp} "
"from saving to the backup directory, use this:"
msgstr "リモート・ファイルのバックアップ機能を「オフ」にして、 @value{tramp} によるバックアップ・ディレクトリへの保存を停止するには、 以下のようにします:"

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3100
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(add-to-list 'backup-directory-alist\n"
"             (cons tramp-file-name-regexp nil))\n"
msgstr ""
"(add-to-list 'backup-directory-alist\n"
"             (cons tramp-file-name-regexp nil))\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3106
msgid ""
"Disabling backups can be targeted to just the @option{su} and @option{sudo} "
"methods:"
msgstr "例えば、 バックアップの無効化は、 @option{su} と @option{sudo} 方式のみを対象にすることが可能です:"

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3116
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(setq backup-enable-predicate\n"
"      (lambda (name)\n"
"        (and (normal-backup-enable-predicate name)\n"
"             (not\n"
"              (let ((method (file-remote-p name 'method)))\n"
"                (when (stringp method)\n"
"                  (member method '(\"su\" \"sudo\"))))))))\n"
msgstr ""
"(setq backup-enable-predicate\n"
"      (lambda (name)\n"
"        (and (normal-backup-enable-predicate name)\n"
"             (not\n"
"              (let ((method (file-remote-p name 'method)))\n"
"                (when (stringp method)\n"
"                  (member method '(\"su\" \"sudo\"))))))))\n"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3119
#, no-wrap
msgid "tramp-backup-directory-alist"
msgstr "tramp-backup-directory-alist"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3126
msgid ""
"Another option is to create better backup file naming with user and host "
"names prefixed to the file name.  For example, transforming @file{/etc/"
"secretfile} to @file{~/.emacs.d/backups/!su:root@@localhost:!etc!"
"secretfile}, set the @value{tramp} user option @code{tramp-backup-directory-"
"alist} from the existing user option @code{backup-directory-alist}."
msgstr "もう 1 つのオプションは、 ファイル名の前にユーザー名とホスト名を付けて、 より適切なバックアップ・ファイル名を命名することです。 たとえば、 @file{/etc/secretfile} を @file{~/.emacs.d/backups/!su:root@@localhost:!etc!secretfile} に変換し、 既存のユーザー・オプション @code{backup-directory-alist} より、 @value{tramp} ユーザー・オプション @code{tramp-backup-directory-alist} を設定します。"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3130
msgid ""
"Then @value{tramp} backs up to a file name that is transformed with a prefix "
"consisting of the DIRECTORY name.  This file name prefixing happens only "
"when the DIRECTORY is an absolute local file name."
msgstr "次に、 @value{tramp} は、 DIRECTORY 名で構成されるプレフィックスで変換されたファイル名にバックアップします。 このファイル名のプレフィックスは、 DIRECTORY が絶対ローカル・ファイル名である場合にのみ発生します。"

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3140
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(add-to-list 'backup-directory-alist\n"
"             (cons \".\" \"~/.emacs.d/backups/\"))\n"
"(customize-set-variable\n"
" 'tramp-backup-directory-alist backup-directory-alist)\n"
msgstr ""
"(add-to-list 'backup-directory-alist\n"
"             (cons \".\" \"~/.emacs.d/backups/\"))\n"
"(customize-set-variable\n"
" 'tramp-backup-directory-alist backup-directory-alist)\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3146
msgid ""
"The backup file name of @file{@trampfn{su,root@@localhost,/etc/secretfile}} "
"would be"
msgstr "@file{@trampfn{su,root@@localhost,/etc/secretfile}} のバックアップ・ファイル名は以下のようになります"

#. type: ifset
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3148
msgid ""
"@file{@trampfn{su,root@@localhost,~/.emacs.d/backups/!su:root@@localhost:!"
"etc!secretfile~}}."
msgstr "@file{@trampfn{su,root@@localhost,~/.emacs.d/backups/!su:root@@localhost:!etc!secretfile~}}."

#. type: ifset
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3151
msgid ""
"@file{@trampfn{su,root@@localhost,~/.emacs.d/backups/![su!root@@localhost]!"
"etc!secretfile~}}."
msgstr "@file{@trampfn{su,root@@localhost,~/.emacs.d/backups/![su!root@@localhost]!etc!secretfile~}}."

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3153
#, no-wrap
msgid "auto-save-file-name-transforms"
msgstr "auto-save-file-name-transforms"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3160
msgid ""
"Just as for backup files, similar issues of file naming affect auto-saving "
"remote files.  Auto-saved files are saved in the directory specified by the "
"user option @code{auto-save-file-name-transforms}.  By default this is set "
"to the local temporary directory.  But in some versions of Debian GNU/Linux, "
"this points to the source directory where the Emacs was compiled.  Reset "
"such values to a valid directory."
msgstr "バックアップ・ファイルと同様に、 ファイルの命名に関する同様の問題がリモート・ファイルの自動保存に影響します。 自動保存されたファイルは、 ユーザー・オプション @code{auto-save-file-name-transforms} で指定されたディレクトリに保存されます。 デフォルトでは、 これはローカルの一時ディレクトリに設定されています。 しかし、 Debian GNU/Linux の一部のバージョンでは、 これは Emacs がコンパイルされたソース・ディレクトリを指します。 そのような値を有効なディレクトリにリセットします。"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3163
msgid ""
"Set @code{auto-save-file-name-transforms} to @code{nil} to save auto-saved "
"files to the same directory as the original file."
msgstr "@code{auto-save-file-name-transforms} を @code{nil} に設定して、 自動保存されたファイルを元のファイルと同じディレクトリに保存します。"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3164
#, no-wrap
msgid "tramp-auto-save-directory"
msgstr "tramp-auto-save-directory"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3167
msgid ""
"Alternatively, set the user option @code{tramp-auto-save-directory} to "
"direct all auto saves to that location."
msgstr "あるいは、 ユーザー・オプション @code{tramp-auto-save-directory} を設定して、 すべての自動保存をその場所に向けます。"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3169
#, no-wrap
msgid "remote-file-name-inhibit-auto-save-visited"
msgstr "remote-file-name-inhibit-auto-save-visited"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3175
msgid ""
"An alternative to @code{auto-save-mode} is @code{auto-save-visited-mode}.  "
"In this mode, auto-saving is identical to explicit saving.  If you want to "
"disable this behavior for remote files, set user option @code{remote-file-"
"name-inhibit-auto-save-visited} to non-@code{nil}."
msgstr "@code{auto-save-mode} の代替は @code{auto-save-visited-mode} です。 このモードでは、 自動保存は明示的保存と同じです。 リモート・ファイルに対してこの動作を無効にしたい場合は、 ユーザーオプション @code{remote-file-name-inhibit-auto-save-visited} を 非 @code{nil} に設定してください。"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3176
#, no-wrap
msgid "lock-file-name-transforms"
msgstr "lock-file-name-transforms"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3182
msgid ""
"And still more issues to handle.  Since @w{Emacs 28}, file locks use a "
"similar user option as auto-save files, called @code{lock-file-name-"
"transforms}.  By default this user option is @code{nil}, meaning to keep "
"file locks in the same directory as the original file."
msgstr "そして、さらに多くの問題を処理する必要があります。 @w{Emacs 28} 以降、 ファイル・ロックは @code{lock-file-name-transforms} と呼ばれる自動保存ファイルと同様のユーザー・オプションを使用します。 デフォルトでは、 このユーザー・オプションは @code{nil} で、 ファイル・ロックを元のファイルと同じディレクトリに保持することを意味します。"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3188
msgid ""
"If you change @code{lock-file-name-transforms} in order to keep file locks "
"for remote files somewhere else, you will lose Emacs's feature to warn you, "
"if a file is changed in parallel from different Emacs sessions, or via "
"different remote connections.  Be careful with such settings."
msgstr "もし、 @code{lock-file-name-transforms}を変更して、 リモート・ファイルのファイル・ロックを別の場所に保持するようにすると、 異なるEmacsセッションや異なるリモート接続から並行してファイルを変更した場合に警告するEmacsの機能が失われます。 このような設定には注意を払ってください。"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3189
#, no-wrap
msgid "remote-file-name-inhibit-locks"
msgstr "remote-file-name-inhibit-locks"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3192
msgid ""
"Setting @code{remote-file-name-inhibit-locks} to non-@code{nil} prevents the "
"creation of remote lock files at all."
msgstr "@code{remote-file-name-inhibit-locks} を 非 @code{nil} に設定すると、 リモート・ロック・ファイルの作成が完全に抑止されます。"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3193
#, no-wrap
msgid "tramp-allow-unsafe-temporary-files"
msgstr "tramp-allow-unsafe-temporary-files"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3199
msgid ""
"Per default, @value{tramp} asks for confirmation if a @samp{root}-owned "
"remote backup, auto-save or lock file has to be written to your local "
"temporary directory.  If you want to suppress this confirmation question, "
"set user option @code{tramp-allow-unsafe-temporary-files} to @code{t}."
msgstr "デフォルトでは、 @value{tramp} は、 @samp{root} 所有のリモート・バックアップまたは、 自動保存または、 ロック・ファイルをローカルの一時ディレクトリに書き込む必要があるかどうかを確認します。 この確認の質問を抑制したい場合は、ユーザー・オプション @code{tramp-allow-unsafe-temporary-files} を @code{t} に設定してください。"

#. type: section
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3202
#, no-wrap
msgid "Protect remote files by encryption"
msgstr "Protect remote files by encryption"

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3203
#, no-wrap
msgid "Encrypt remote directories"
msgstr "Encrypt remote directories"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3207
msgid ""
"@strong{Note}: File encryption in @value{tramp} is experimental, don't use "
"it in production systems!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3213
msgid ""
"Sometimes, it is desirable to protect files located on remote directories, "
"like cloud storages.  In order to do this, you might instruct @value{tramp} "
"to encrypt all files copied to a given remote directory, and to decrypt such "
"files when accessing.  This includes both file contents and file names."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3217
msgid ""
"@value{tramp} does this transparently.  Although both files and file names "
"are encrypted on the remote side, they are accessible inside Emacs as they "
"wouldn't be transformed as such."
msgstr ""

#. type: command{#1}
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3218
#, no-wrap
msgid "encfs"
msgstr ""

#. type: command{#1}
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3219
#, no-wrap
msgid "encfsctl"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3225
msgid ""
"Internally, @value{tramp} uses the @command{encfs} package.  Therefore, this "
"feature is available only if this package is installed on the local host.  "
"@value{tramp} does not keep and @samp{encfs mountpoint} permanently.  "
"Instead, it encrypts / decrypts files and file names on the fly, using "
"@command{encfsctl}."
msgstr ""

#. type: deffn
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3226
#, no-wrap
msgid "Command tramp-crypt-add-directory name"
msgstr ""

#. type: deffn
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3231
msgid ""
"This command marks the existing remote directory @var{name} for encryption.  "
"Files in that directory and all subdirectories will be encrypted before "
"copying to, and decrypted after copying from that directory.  File and "
"directory names will be also encrypted."
msgstr ""

#. type: defopt
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3233
#, no-wrap
msgid "tramp-crypt-encfs-option"
msgstr "tramp-crypt-encfs-option"

#. type: defopt
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3239
msgid ""
"If a remote directory is marked for encryption, it is initialized via "
"@command{encfs} the very first time a file in this directory is accessed.  "
"This user option controls, which default @command{encfs} configuration "
"option will be selected, it can be @t{\"--standard\"} or @t{\"--paranoia"
"\"}.  See the @samp{encfs(1)} man page for details."
msgstr ""

#. type: defopt
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3243
msgid ""
"However, @value{tramp} must adapt these configuration sets.  The "
"@code{chainedNameIV} configuration option must be disabled; otherwise "
"@value{tramp} couldn't handle file name encryption transparently."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3256
msgid ""
"A password protected @option{encfs} configuration file is created the very "
"first time you access an encrypted remote directory.  It is kept in your "
"@code{user-emacs-directory} with the url-encoded directory name as part of "
"the basename, and @file{encfs6.xml} as suffix.  If you, for example, mark "
"the remote directory @file{@trampfn{nextcloud,user@@host,/path/to/dir}} for "
"encryption, the configuration file is saved as @file{tramp-%2Fnextcloud"
"%3Auser%40host%3A%2Fpath%2Fto%2Fdir%2F.encfs6.xml} in @code{user-emacs-"
"directory}.  Do not lose this file and the corresponding password; otherwise "
"there is no way to decrypt your encrypted files."
msgstr ""

#. type: defopt
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3257
#, no-wrap
msgid "tramp-crypt-save-encfs-config-remote"
msgstr "tramp-crypt-save-encfs-config-remote"

#. type: defopt
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3265
msgid ""
"If this user option is non-@code{nil} (the default), the @option{encfs} "
"configuration file @file{.encfs6.xml} is also kept in the encrypted remote "
"directory.  It depends on you, whether you regard the password protection of "
"this file as sufficient.  The advantage would be, that such a remote "
"directory could be accessed by different Emacs sessions, different users, "
"without presharing the configuration file between the users."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3276
msgid ""
"The command @command{encfsctl}, the workhorse for encryption / decryption, "
"needs the configuration file password every call.  Therefore, it is "
"recommend to cache this password in Emacs.  This can be done using "
"@code{auth-sources}, @ref{Using an authentication file}.  An entry needs the "
"url-encoded directory name as machine, your local user name as user, and the "
"password.  The port is optional, if given it must be the string @t{\"crypt"
"\"}.  The example above would require the following entry in the "
"authentication file (@t{\"yourname\"} is the result of @code{(user-login-"
"name)}):"
msgstr ""

#. type: example
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3280
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"machine %2Fnextcloud%3Auser%40host%3A%2Fpath%2Fto%2Fdir%2F \\\n"
"        login yourname port crypt password geheim\n"
msgstr ""
"machine %2Fnextcloud%3Auser%40host%3A%2Fpath%2Fto%2Fdir%2F \\\n"
"        login yourname port crypt password geheim\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3286
msgid ""
"If you use a remote file name with a quoted localname part, this localname "
"and the corresponding file will not be encrypted / decrypted.  If you have "
"an encrypted remote directory @file{@trampfn{nextcloud,user@@host,/path/to/"
"dir}}, the command"
msgstr ""

#. type: example
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3289
#, no-wrap
msgid "@kbd{C-x d @trampfn{nextcloud,user@@host,/path/to/dir}}\n"
msgstr "@kbd{C-x d @trampfn{nextcloud,user@@host,/path/to/dir}}\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3294
msgid ""
"will show the directory listing with the plain file names, and the command"
msgstr ""

#. type: example
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3297
#, no-wrap
msgid "@kbd{C-x d @trampfn{nextcloud,user@@host,/:/path/to/dir}}\n"
msgstr "@kbd{C-x d @trampfn{nextcloud,user@@host,/:/path/to/dir}}\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3304
msgid ""
"will show the directory listing with the encrypted file names, and visiting "
"a file will show its encrypted contents.  However, it is highly discouraged "
"to mix encrypted and not encrypted files in the same directory."
msgstr ""

#. type: deffn
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3305
#, no-wrap
msgid "Command tramp-crypt-remove-directory name"
msgstr ""

#. type: deffn
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3309
msgid ""
"This command should be used to indicate that files in @code{name} should no "
"longer be encrypted.  Existing encrypted files and subdirectories will "
"remain encrypted."
msgstr ""

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3314
#, no-wrap
msgid "using @value{tramp}"
msgstr "using @value{tramp}"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3322
msgid ""
"@value{tramp} operates transparently, accessing remote files as if they are "
"local.  However, @value{tramp} employs a formalized remote file naming "
"syntax to perform its functions transparently.  This syntax consists of many "
"parts specifying access methods, authentication, host names, and file "
"names.  Ange FTP uses a similar syntax."
msgstr ""

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3323
#, no-wrap
msgid "type-ahead"
msgstr "type-ahead"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3332
msgid ""
"Unlike opening local files in Emacs, which are instantaneous, opening remote "
"files in @value{tramp} is slower at first.  Sometimes there is a noticeable "
"delay before the prompts for passwords or authentication appear in the "
"minibuffer.  Hitting @kbd{@key{RET}} or other keys during this gap will be "
"processed by Emacs.  This type-ahead facility is a feature of Emacs that may "
"cause missed prompts when using @value{tramp}."
msgstr ""

#. type: section
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3349
#, no-wrap
msgid "@value{tramp} file name conventions"
msgstr "@value{tramp} file name conventions"

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3351
#, no-wrap
msgid "file name examples"
msgstr "file name examples"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3355
msgid ""
"@file{@trampfn{method,host,/path/to/file}} opens file @var{/path/to/file} on "
"the remote host @var{host}, using the method @var{method}."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3358
#, no-wrap
msgid "@value{prefix}ssh@value{postfixhop}melancholia@value{postfix}.emacs"
msgstr "@value{prefix}ssh@value{postfixhop}melancholia@value{postfix}.emacs"

#. type: table
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3361
msgid ""
"For the file @file{.emacs} located in the home directory, on the host "
"@code{melancholia}, using method @code{ssh}."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3362
#, no-wrap
msgid "@value{prefix}ssh@value{postfixhop}melancholia.danann.net@value{postfix}.emacs"
msgstr "@value{prefix}ssh@value{postfixhop}melancholia.danann.net@value{postfix}.emacs"

#. type: table
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3365
msgid ""
"For the file @file{.emacs} specified using the fully qualified domain name "
"of the host."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3366
#, no-wrap
msgid "@value{prefix}ssh@value{postfixhop}melancholia@value{postfix}~/.emacs"
msgstr ""

#. type: table
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3368
msgid ""
"For the file @file{.emacs} specified using the @file{~}, which is expanded."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3369
#, no-wrap
msgid "@value{prefix}ssh@value{postfixhop}melancholia@value{postfix}~daniel/.emacs"
msgstr "@value{prefix}ssh@value{postfixhop}melancholia@value{postfix}~daniel/.emacs"

#. type: table
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3373
msgid ""
"For the file @file{.emacs} located in @code{daniel}'s home directory on the "
"host, @code{melancholia}.  The @file{~<user>} construct is expanded to the "
"home directory of that user on the remote host."
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3374
#, no-wrap
msgid "@value{prefix}ssh@value{postfixhop}melancholia@value{postfix}/etc/squid.conf"
msgstr "@value{prefix}ssh@value{postfixhop}melancholia@value{postfix}/etc/squid.conf"

#. type: table
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3376
msgid "For the file @file{/etc/squid.conf} on the host @code{melancholia}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3382
msgid ""
"@var{host} can take IPv4 or IPv6 address, as in "
"@file{@trampfn{ssh,127.0.0.1,.emacs}} or @file{@trampfn{ssh,"
"@value{ipv6prefix}::1@value{ipv6postfix},.emacs}}."
msgstr ""

#. type: ifset
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3385
msgid ""
"For syntactical reasons, IPv6 addresses must be embedded in square brackets "
"@file{@value{ipv6prefix}} and @file{@value{ipv6postfix}}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3391
msgid ""
"By default, @value{tramp} will use the current local user name as the remote "
"user name for log in to the remote host.  Specifying a different name using "
"the proper syntax will override this default behavior: @file{@trampfn{method,"
"user@@host,path/to/file}}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3395
msgid ""
"@file{@trampfn{ssh,daniel@@melancholia,.emacs}} is for file @file{.emacs} in "
"@code{daniel}'s home directory on the host, @code{melancholia}, accessing "
"via method @code{ssh}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3398
msgid ""
"For specifying port numbers, affix @file{#<port>} to the host name.  For "
"example: @file{@trampfn{ssh,daniel@@melancholia#42,.emacs}}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3401
msgid ""
"All method, user name, host name, port number and local name parts are "
"optional, @xref{Default Method}, @xref{Default User}, @xref{Default Host}."
msgstr ""

#. type: ifset
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3404
msgid ""
"For syntactical reasons, the default method must be indicated by the pseudo "
"method @file{-}."
msgstr ""

#. type: node
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3408
#, no-wrap
msgid "Change file name syntax"
msgstr "Change file name syntax"

#. type: section
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3409
#, no-wrap
msgid "Alternative file name syntax"
msgstr "Alternative file name syntax"

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3410
#, no-wrap
msgid "change file name syntax"
msgstr "change file name syntax"

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3411
#, no-wrap
msgid "alternative file name syntax"
msgstr "alternative file name syntax"

#. type: ifset
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3416
msgid ""
"The syntax described in @ref{File name syntax} is the @code{default} syntax, "
"which is active after Emacs startup.  However, this can be changed."
msgstr ""

#. type: deffn
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3417
#, no-wrap
msgid "Command tramp-change-syntax syntax"
msgstr ""

#. type: deffn
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3420
msgid ""
"This command changes the syntax @value{tramp} uses for remote file names.  "
"Beside the @code{default} value, @var{syntax} can be"
msgstr ""

#. type: code{#1}
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3422
#, no-wrap
