#. type: section
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3571
#, no-wrap
msgid "Declaring multiple hops in the file name"
msgstr "Declaring multiple hops in the file name"

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3572
#, no-wrap
msgid "multi-hop, ad-hoc"
msgstr "multi-hop, ad-hoc"

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3573
#, no-wrap
msgid "proxy hosts, ad-hoc"
msgstr "proxy hosts, ad-hoc"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3578
msgid ""
"@value{tramp} file name syntax can accommodate ad-hoc specification of "
"multiple proxies without using @code{tramp-default-proxies-alist} "
"configuration setup (@pxref{Multi-hops})."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3584
msgid ""
"Each proxy is specified using the same syntax as the remote host "
"specification minus the file name part.  Each hop is separated by a "
"@samp{|}.  Chain the proxies from the starting host to the destination "
"remote host name and file name.  For example, hopping over a single proxy "
"@samp{bird@@bastion} to a remote file on @samp{you@@remotehost}:"
msgstr ""

#. type: example
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3589
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"@kbd{C-x C-f @value{prefix}ssh@value{postfixhop}bird@@bastion|@c\n"
"ssh@value{postfixhop}you@@remotehost@value{postfix}/path @key{RET}}\n"
msgstr ""
"@kbd{C-x C-f @value{prefix}ssh@value{postfixhop}bird@@bastion|@c\n"
"ssh@value{postfixhop}you@@remotehost@value{postfix}/path @key{RET}}\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3592
msgid "Each involved method must be an inline method (@pxref{Inline methods})."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3601
msgid ""
"@value{tramp} adds the ad-hoc definitions on the fly to @code{tramp-default-"
"proxies-alist} and is available for re-use during that Emacs session.  "
"Subsequent @value{tramp} connections to the same remote host can then use "
"the shortcut form: @samp{@trampfn{ssh,you@@remotehost,/path}}.  Ad-hoc "
"definitions are removed from @code{tramp-default-proxies-alist} via the "
"command @kbd{M-x tramp-cleanup-all-connections @key{RET}} (@pxref{Cleanup "
"remote connections})."
msgstr ""

#. type: defopt
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3602
#, no-wrap
msgid "tramp-save-ad-hoc-proxies"
msgstr "tramp-save-ad-hoc-proxies"

#. type: defopt
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3606
msgid ""
"For ad-hoc definitions to be saved automatically in @code{tramp-default-"
"proxies-alist} for future Emacs sessions, set @code{tramp-save-ad-hoc-"
"proxies} to non-@code{nil}."
msgstr ""

#. type: lisp
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3609
#, no-wrap
msgid "(customize-set-variable 'tramp-save-ad-hoc-proxies t)\n"
msgstr "(customize-set-variable 'tramp-save-ad-hoc-proxies t)\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3617
msgid ""
"Ad-hoc proxies can take patterns @code{%h} or @code{%u} like in @code{tramp-"
"default-proxies-alist}.  The following file name expands to user @samp{root} "
"on host @samp{remotehost}, starting with an @option{ssh} session on host "
"@samp{remotehost}: @samp{@trampfn{ssh@value{postfixhop}%h|su,remotehost,}}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3622
msgid ""
"On the other hand, if a trailing hop does not specify a host name, the host "
"name of the previous hop is reused.  Therefore, the following file name is "
"equivalent to the previous example: @samp{@trampfn{ssh@value{postfixhop}"
"remotehost|su,,}}."
msgstr ""

#. type: section
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3625
#, no-wrap
msgid "Expanding @file{~} to home directory"
msgstr "Expanding @file{~} to home directory"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3630
msgid ""
"Home directories on remote hosts can be typed as tilde @file{~}.  If "
"possible, they are expanded to the remote user's home directory on the "
"remote host.  Example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3635
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"@trampfn{ssh,user@@host,~}\n"
"@result{} @trampfn{ssh,user@@host,/home/user}\n"
msgstr ""
"@trampfn{ssh,user@@host,~}\n"
"@result{} @trampfn{ssh,user@@host,/home/user}\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3641
msgid ""
"This works in general for @option{ssh}-like methods, and for "
"@option{sudoedit}.  These methods allow also the home directory expansion "
"for another user, like"
msgstr ""

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3646
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"@trampfn{sudoedit,,~otheruser}\n"
"@result{} @trampfn{sudoedit,root@@localhost,/home/otheruser}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3654
msgid ""
"For other methods, a home directory can be expanded only if supported.  This "
"happens for example for the @option{sftp} method.  Methods, which require a "
"share directory in the remote file name (@option{afp}, @option{smb}), use "
"the value of this share directory as home directory:"
msgstr ""

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3659
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"@trampfn{smb,user@@host,~}\n"
"@result{} @trampfn{smb,user@@host,/share}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3665
msgid ""
"Since Tramp cannot know in advance which share directory is intended to use, "
"this expansion can be applied only when a share directory has been used "
"already."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3671
msgid ""
"The methods @option{adb}, @option{rclone} and @option{sshfs} do not support "
"home directory expansion at all.  However, @value{tramp} keeps the home "
"directory in the cache.  Therefore, those methods could be configured to "
"expand a home directory via a connection property, @xref{Predefined "
"connection information}.  Example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3677
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(add-to-list 'tramp-connection-properties\n"
"             (list (regexp-quote \"@trampfn{sshfs,user@@randomhost.your.domain,}\")\n"
"                   \"~user\" \"/home/user\"))\n"
msgstr ""
"(add-to-list 'tramp-connection-properties\n"
"             (list (regexp-quote \"@trampfn{sshfs,user@@randomhost.your.domain,}\")\n"
"                   \"~user\" \"/home/user\"))\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3682
msgid ""
"When your remote file name does not contain a @samp{user} part, the "
"connection property @t{\"~\"} must be used instead."
msgstr ""

#. type: section
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3685
#, no-wrap
msgid "Integration with other Emacs packages"
msgstr "Integration with other Emacs packages"

#. type: code{#1}
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3686
#, no-wrap
msgid "compile"
msgstr ""

#. type: code{#1}
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3687
#, no-wrap
msgid "recompile"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3692
msgid ""
"@value{tramp} supports starting new running processes on the remote host for "
"discovering remote file names.  Emacs packages on the remote host need no "
"specific modifications for @value{tramp}'s use."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3696
msgid ""
"This type of integration does not work with the @option{ftp} method, and "
"does not support the pty association as specified in @code{start-file-"
"process}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3699
msgid ""
"@code{process-file} and @code{start-file-process} work on the remote host "
"when the variable @code{default-directory} is remote:"
msgstr ""

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3705
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(let ((default-directory \"/ssh:remote.host:\"))\n"
"  (start-file-process \"grep\" (get-buffer-create \"*grep*\")\n"
"                      \"/bin/sh\" \"-c\" \"grep -e tramp *\"))\n"
msgstr ""
"(let ((default-directory \"/ssh:remote.host:\"))\n"
"  (start-file-process \"grep\" (get-buffer-create \"*grep*\")\n"
"                      \"/bin/sh\" \"-c\" \"grep -e tramp *\"))\n"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3708
#, no-wrap
msgid "process-file-return-signal-string"
msgstr "process-file-return-signal-string"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3718
msgid ""
"For a local process, @code{process-file} returns either the exit code of the "
"process, or a string describing a signal, when the process has been "
"interrupted.  Since it cannot be determined reliably whether a remote "
"process has been interrupted, @code{process-file} will always returns the "
"exit code for it.  When the user option @code{process-file-return-signal-"
"string} is non-@code{nil}, @code{process-file} treats all exit codes greater "
"than 128 as an indication that the process has been interrupted, and returns "
"a corresponding string."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3723
msgid ""
"This remote process handling does not apply to @acronym{GVFS} (@pxref{GVFS-"
"based methods}) because the remote file system is mounted on the local host "
"and @value{tramp} accesses it by changing the @code{default-directory}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3729
msgid ""
"@value{tramp} starts a remote process when a command is executed in a remote "
"file or directory buffer.  As of now, these packages have been integrated to "
"work with @value{tramp}: @file{shell.el}, @file{eshell.el}, @file{compile."
"el} (commands like @code{compile} and @code{grep}) and @file{gud.el} "
"(@code{gdb} or @code{perldb})."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3737
msgid ""
"@value{tramp} always modifies the @env{INSIDE_EMACS} environment variable "
"for remote processes.  By default, this environment variable shows the Emacs "
"version.  @value{tramp} adds its own version string, so it looks like "
"@samp{27.2,tramp:2.4.5.1}.  However, other packages might also add their "
"name to this environment variable, like @samp{27.2,comint,tramp:2.4.5.1}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3742
msgid ""
"For @value{tramp} to find the command on the remote, it must be accessible "
"through the default search path as setup by @value{tramp} upon first "
"connection.  Alternatively, use an absolute path or extend @code{tramp-"
"remote-path} (@pxref{Remote programs}):"
msgstr ""

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3747
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(add-to-list 'tramp-remote-path \"~/bin\")\n"
"(add-to-list 'tramp-remote-path \"/appli/pub/bin\")\n"
msgstr ""
"(add-to-list 'tramp-remote-path \"~/bin\")\n"
"(add-to-list 'tramp-remote-path \"/appli/pub/bin\")\n"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3750
#, no-wrap
msgid "tramp-remote-process-environment"
msgstr "tramp-remote-process-environment"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3756
msgid ""
"Customize user option @code{tramp-remote-process-environment} to suit the "
"remote program's environment for the remote host.  @code{tramp-remote-"
"process-environment} is a list of strings structured similar to "
"@code{process-environment}, where each element is a string of the form "
"@samp{ENVVARNAME=VALUE}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3760
msgid ""
"To avoid any conflicts with local host environment variables set through "
"local configuration files, such as @file{~/.profile}, use @samp{ENVVARNAME=} "
"to unset them for the remote environment."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3763
msgid "Use @code{add-to-list} to add entries:"
msgstr ""

#. type: lisp
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3766
#, no-wrap
msgid "(add-to-list 'tramp-remote-process-environment \"JAVA_HOME=/opt/java\")\n"
msgstr "(add-to-list 'tramp-remote-process-environment \"JAVA_HOME=/opt/java\")\n"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3768
#, no-wrap
msgid "HISTORY@r{, environment variable}"
msgstr "HISTORY@r{, environment variable}"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3776
msgid ""
"Modifying or deleting already existing values in the @code{tramp-remote-"
"process-environment} list may not be feasible on restricted remote hosts.  "
"For example, some system administrators disallow changing @env{HISTORY} "
"environment variable.  To accommodate such restrictions when using "
"@value{tramp}, fix the @code{tramp-remote-process-environment} by the "
"following code in the local @file{.emacs} file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3782
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(let ((process-environment tramp-remote-process-environment))\n"
"  (setenv \"HISTORY\" nil)\n"
"  (setq tramp-remote-process-environment process-environment))\n"
msgstr ""
"(let ((process-environment tramp-remote-process-environment))\n"
"  (setenv \"HISTORY\" nil)\n"
"  (setq tramp-remote-process-environment process-environment))\n"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3785
#, no-wrap
msgid "ENV@r{, environment variable}"
msgstr "ENV@r{, environment variable}"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3789
msgid ""
"Setting the @env{ENV} environment variable instructs some shells to read an "
"initialization file.  By default, @value{tramp} disables this.  You can "
"override this behavior by evaluating"
msgstr ""

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3795
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(let ((process-environment tramp-remote-process-environment))\n"
"  (setenv \"ENV\" \"$HOME/.profile\")\n"
"  (setq tramp-remote-process-environment process-environment))\n"
msgstr ""
"(let ((process-environment tramp-remote-process-environment))\n"
"  (setenv \"ENV\" \"$HOME/.profile\")\n"
"  (setq tramp-remote-process-environment process-environment))\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3805
msgid ""
"In addition to @code{tramp-remote-process-environment}, you can set "
"environment variables for individual remote process calls by let-binding "
"@code{process-environment}.  @value{tramp} applies any entries not present "
"in the global default value of @code{process-environment} (overriding "
"@code{tramp-remote-process-environment} settings, if they conflict).  For "
"example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3810
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(let ((process-environment (cons \"HGPLAIN=1\" process-environment)))\n"
"  (process-file @dots{}))\n"
msgstr ""
"(let ((process-environment (cons \"HGPLAIN=1\" process-environment)))\n"
"  (process-file @dots{}))\n"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3813
#, no-wrap
msgid "HGPLAIN@r{, environment variable}"
msgstr "HGPLAIN@r{, environment variable}"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3818
msgid ""
"Let-binding in this way works regardless of whether the process to be called "
"is local or remote, since @value{tramp} would add just the @env{HGPLAIN} "
"setting and local processes would take whole value of @code{process-"
"environment} along with the new value of @env{HGPLAIN}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3821
msgid ""
"For integrating other Emacs packages so @value{tramp} can execute remotely, "
"please file a bug report.  @xref{Bug Reports}."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3823
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running remote programs that create local X11 windows"
msgstr "Running remote programs that create local X11 windows"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3825
#, no-wrap
msgid "DISPLAY@r{, environment variable}"
msgstr "DISPLAY@r{, environment variable}"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3829
msgid ""
"To allow a remote program to create an X11 window on the local host, set the "
"@env{DISPLAY} environment variable for the remote host as follows in the "
"local @file{.emacs} file:"
msgstr ""

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3834
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(add-to-list 'tramp-remote-process-environment\n"
"             (format \"DISPLAY=%s\" (getenv \"DISPLAY\")))\n"
msgstr ""
"(add-to-list 'tramp-remote-process-environment\n"
"             (format \"DISPLAY=%s\" (getenv \"DISPLAY\")))\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3844
msgid ""
"@code{(getenv \"DISPLAY\")} should return a recognizable name for the local "
"host that the remote host can redirect X11 window interactions.  If querying "
"for a recognizable name is not possible for whatever reason, then replace "
"@code{(getenv \"DISPLAY\")} with a hard-coded, fixed name.  Note that using "
"@code{:0} for X11 display name here will not work as expected."
msgstr ""

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3845
#, no-wrap
msgid "ForwardX11@r{, ssh option}"
msgstr "ForwardX11@r{, ssh option}"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3846
#, no-wrap
msgid "ForwardX11Trusted@r{, ssh option}"
msgstr "ForwardX11Trusted@r{, ssh option}"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3850
msgid ""
"An alternate approach is specify @option{ForwardX11 yes} or "
"@option{ForwardX11Trusted yes} in @file{~/.ssh/config} on the local host."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3852
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running @code{shell} on a remote host"
msgstr "Running @code{shell} on a remote host"

#. type: code{#1}
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3853
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3859
msgid ""
"Set @code{explicit-shell-file-name} to the appropriate shell name when using "
"@value{tramp} between two hosts with different operating systems, such as "
"@samp{windows-nt} and @samp{gnu/linux}.  This option ensures the correct "
"name of the remote shell program."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3862
msgid ""
"When @code{explicit-shell-file-name} is equal to @code{nil}, calling "
"@code{shell} interactively will prompt for a shell name."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3865
msgid ""
"You could use connection-local variables for setting different values of "
"@code{explicit-shell-file-name} for different remote hosts."
msgstr ""

#. type: ifinfo
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3867 ../texi/tramp.texi:4191
msgid "@xref{Connection Variables, , , emacs}."
msgstr ""

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3875
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(connection-local-set-profile-variables\n"
"  'remote-bash\n"
"  '((explicit-shell-file-name . \"/bin/bash\")\n"
"    (explicit-bash-args . (\"-i\"))))\n"
msgstr ""
"(connection-local-set-profile-variables\n"
"  'remote-bash\n"
"  '((explicit-shell-file-name . \"/bin/bash\")\n"
"    (explicit-bash-args . (\"-i\"))))\n"

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3882
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(connection-local-set-profile-variables\n"
"  'remote-ksh\n"
"  '((explicit-shell-file-name . \"/bin/ksh\")\n"
"    (explicit-ksh-args . (\"-i\"))))\n"
msgstr ""
"(connection-local-set-profile-variables\n"
"  'remote-ksh\n"
"  '((explicit-shell-file-name . \"/bin/ksh\")\n"
"    (explicit-ksh-args . (\"-i\"))))\n"

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3888
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(connection-local-set-profiles\n"
"  '(:application tramp :protocol \"ssh\" :machine \"localhost\")\n"
"  'remote-bash)\n"
msgstr ""
"(connection-local-set-profiles\n"
"  '(:application tramp :protocol \"ssh\" :machine \"localhost\")\n"
"  'remote-bash)\n"

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3895
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(connection-local-set-profiles\n"
"  `(:application tramp :protocol \"sudo\"\n"
"    :user \"root\" :machine ,(system-name))\n"
"  'remote-ksh)\n"
msgstr ""
"(connection-local-set-profiles\n"
"  `(:application tramp :protocol \"sudo\"\n"
"    :user \"root\" :machine ,(system-name))\n"
"  'remote-ksh)\n"

#. type: subsection
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3899
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running @code{shell-command} on a remote host"
msgstr "Running @code{shell-command} on a remote host"

#. type: code{#1}
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3900
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell-command"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3905
msgid ""
"@code{shell-command} executes commands synchronously or asynchronously on "
"remote hosts and displays output in buffers on the local host.  Example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3910
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"@kbd{C-x C-f @trampfn{sudo,,} @key{RET}}\n"
"@kbd{M-& tail -f /var/log/syslog.log @key{RET}}\n"
msgstr ""
"@kbd{C-x C-f @trampfn{sudo,,} @key{RET}}\n"
"@kbd{M-& tail -f /var/log/syslog.log @key{RET}}\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3915
msgid ""
"@command{tail} command outputs continuously to the local buffer whose name "
"is the value of the variable @code{shell-command-buffer-name-async}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3918
msgid ""
"@kbd{M-x auto-revert-tail-mode @key{RET}} runs similarly showing continuous "
"output."
msgstr ""

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3919
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell-file-name"
msgstr "shell-file-name"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3920
#, no-wrap
msgid "shell-command-switch"
msgstr "shell-command-switch"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3928
msgid ""
"@code{shell-command} uses the user option @code{shell-file-name} and the "
"variable @code{shell-command-switch} in order to determine which shell to "
"run.  For remote hosts, their default values are @file{/bin/sh} and @option{-"
"c}, respectively (except for the @option{adb} method, which uses @file{/"
"system/bin/sh}).  Like the variables in the previous section, these "
"variables can be changed via connection-local variables."
msgstr ""

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3929
#, no-wrap
msgid "async-shell-command-width"
msgstr "async-shell-command-width"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3930
#, no-wrap
msgid "COLUMNS@r{, environment variable}"
msgstr "COLUMNS@r{, environment variable}"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3937
msgid ""
"If Emacs supports the user option @code{async-shell-command-width} (since "
"@w{Emacs 27}), @value{tramp} cares about its value for asynchronous shell "
"commands.  It specifies the number of display columns for command output.  "
"For synchronous shell commands, a similar effect can be achieved by adding "
"the environment variable @env{COLUMNS} to @code{tramp-remote-process-"
"environment}."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3939
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running @code{eshell} on a remote host"
msgstr "Running @code{eshell} on a remote host"

#. type: code{#1}
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3940
#, no-wrap
msgid "eshell"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3947
msgid ""
"@value{tramp} is integrated into @file{eshell.el}, which enables interactive "
"eshell sessions on remote hosts at the command prompt.  You must add the "
"module @code{eshell-tramp} to @code{eshell-modules-list}.  Here's a sample "
"interaction after opening @kbd{M-x eshell @key{RET}} on a remote host:"
msgstr ""

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3958
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"@b{~ $} cd @trampfn{sudo,,/etc} @key{RET}\n"
"@b{@trampfn{sudo,root@@host,/etc} $} hostname @key{RET}\n"
"host\n"
"@b{@trampfn{sudo,root@@host,/etc} $} id @key{RET}\n"
"uid=0(root) gid=0(root) groups=0(root)\n"
"@b{@trampfn{sudo,root@@host,/etc} $} find-file shadow @key{RET}\n"
"#<buffer shadow>\n"
"@b{@trampfn{sudo,root@@host,/etc} $}\n"
msgstr ""
"@b{~ $} cd @trampfn{sudo,,/etc} @key{RET}\n"
"@b{@trampfn{sudo,root@@host,/etc} $} hostname @key{RET}\n"
"host\n"
"@b{@trampfn{sudo,root@@host,/etc} $} id @key{RET}\n"
"uid=0(root) gid=0(root) groups=0(root)\n"
"@b{@trampfn{sudo,root@@host,/etc} $} find-file shadow @key{RET}\n"
"#<buffer shadow>\n"
"@b{@trampfn{sudo,root@@host,/etc} $}\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3965
msgid ""
"@code{eshell} added custom @code{su} and @code{sudo} commands that set the "
"default directory correctly for the @file{*eshell*} buffer.  @value{tramp} "
"silently updates @code{tramp-default-proxies-alist} with an entry for this "
"directory (@pxref{Multi-hops}):"
msgstr ""

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3973
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"@b{~ $} cd @trampfn{ssh,user@@remotehost,/etc} @key{RET}\n"
"@b{@trampfn{ssh,user@@remotehost,/etc} $} find-file shadow @key{RET}\n"
"File is not readable: @trampfn{ssh,user@@remotehost,/etc/shadow}\n"
"@b{@trampfn{ssh,user@@remotehost,/etc} $} sudo find-file shadow @key{RET}\n"
"#<buffer shadow>\n"
msgstr ""
"@b{~ $} cd @trampfn{ssh,user@@remotehost,/etc} @key{RET}\n"
"@b{@trampfn{ssh,user@@remotehost,/etc} $} find-file shadow @key{RET}\n"
"File is not readable: @trampfn{ssh,user@@remotehost,/etc/shadow}\n"
"@b{@trampfn{ssh,user@@remotehost,/etc} $} sudo find-file shadow @key{RET}\n"
"#<buffer shadow>\n"

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3980
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"@b{@trampfn{ssh,user@@remotehost,/etc} $} su - @key{RET}\n"
"@b{@trampfn{su,root@@remotehost,/root} $} id @key{RET}\n"
"uid=0(root) gid=0(root) groups=0(root)\n"
"@b{@trampfn{su,root@@remotehost,/root} $}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3985
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running a debugger on a remote host"
msgstr "Running a debugger on a remote host"

#. type: file{#1}
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3986
#, no-wrap
msgid "gud.el"
msgstr ""

#. type: code{#1}
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3987
#, no-wrap
msgid "gdb"
msgstr ""

#. type: code{#1}
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3988
#, no-wrap
msgid "perldb"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3991
msgid "@file{gud.el} provides a unified interface to symbolic"
msgstr ""

#. type: ifinfo
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3993
msgid "debuggers (@pxref{Debuggers, , , emacs})."
msgstr ""

#. type: ifnotinfo
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3996
msgid "debuggers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:3999
msgid ""
"@value{tramp} can run debug on remote hosts by calling @code{gdb} with a "
"remote file name:"
msgstr ""

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4004
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"@kbd{M-x gdb @key{RET}}\n"
"@b{Run gdb (like this):} gdb -i=mi @trampfn{ssh,host,~/myprog} @key{RET}\n"
msgstr ""
"@kbd{M-x gdb @key{RET}}\n"
"@b{Run gdb (like this):} gdb -i=mi @trampfn{ssh,host,~/myprog} @key{RET}\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4010
msgid ""
"Since the remote @code{gdb} and @code{gdb-inferior} processes do not belong "
"to the same process group on the remote host, there will be a warning, which "
"can be ignored:"
msgstr ""

#. type: example
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4013
#, no-wrap
msgid "&\"warning: GDB: Failed to set controlling terminal: Operation not permitted\\n\"\n"
msgstr "&\"warning: GDB: Failed to set controlling terminal: Operation not permitted\\n\"\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4018
msgid ""
"As consequence, there will be restrictions in I/O of the process to be "
"debugged."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4022
msgid ""
"Relative file names are based on the remote default directory.  When "
"@file{myprog.pl} exists in @file{@trampfn{ssh,host,/home/user}}, valid calls "
"include:"
msgstr ""

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4027
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"@kbd{M-x perldb @key{RET}}\n"
"@b{Run perldb (like this):} perl -d myprog.pl @key{RET}\n"
msgstr ""
"@kbd{M-x perldb @key{RET}}\n"
"@b{Run perldb (like this):} perl -d myprog.pl @key{RET}\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4032
msgid ""
"Just the local part of a remote file name, such as @command{perl -d /home/"
"user/myprog.pl}, is not possible."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4035
msgid ""
"Arguments of the program to be debugged must be literal, can take relative "
"or absolute paths, but not remote paths."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4037
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running remote processes on MS Windows hosts"
msgstr "Running remote processes on MS Windows hosts"

#. type: command{#1}
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4038
#, no-wrap
msgid "winexe"
msgstr ""

#. type: command{#1}
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4039
#, no-wrap
msgid "powershell"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4044
msgid ""
"@command{winexe} runs processes on a remote MS Windows host, and "
"@value{tramp} can use it for @code{process-file} and @code{start-file-"
"process}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4048
msgid ""
"@code{tramp-smb-winexe-program} specifies the local @command{winexe} "
"command.  Powershell V2.0 on the remote host is required to run processes "
"triggered from @value{tramp}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4052
msgid ""
"@code{explicit-shell-file-name} and @code{explicit-*-args} have to be set "
"properly so @kbd{M-x shell @key{RET}} can open a proper remote shell on a MS "
"Windows host.  To open @command{cmd}, set it as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4057
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(setq explicit-shell-file-name \"cmd\"\n"
"      explicit-cmd-args '(\"/q\"))\n"
msgstr ""
"(setq explicit-shell-file-name \"cmd\"\n"
"      explicit-cmd-args '(\"/q\"))\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4062
msgid "To open @command{powershell} as a remote shell, use this:"
msgstr ""

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4067
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(setq explicit-shell-file-name \"powershell\"\n"
"      explicit-powershell-args '(\"-file\" \"-\"))\n"
msgstr ""
"(setq explicit-shell-file-name \"powershell\"\n"
"      explicit-powershell-args '(\"-file\" \"-\"))\n"

#. type: subsection
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4071
#, no-wrap
msgid "Remote process connection type"
msgstr "Remote process connection type"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4072
#, no-wrap
msgid "process-connection-type"
msgstr "process-connection-type"

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4073
#, no-wrap
msgid "tramp-process-connection-type"
msgstr "tramp-process-connection-type"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4085
msgid ""
"Asynchronous processes behave differently based on whether they use a pseudo "
"tty or not.  This is controlled by the variable @code{process-connection-"
"type}, which can be @code{t} or @code{pty} (use a pseudo tty), or @code{nil} "
"or @code{pipe} (don't use one).  @value{tramp} is based on running shells on "
"the remote host, which requires a pseudo tty.  Therefore, it declares the "
"variable @code{tramp-process-connection-type}, which carries this "
"information for remote processes.  Its default value is @code{t}, and there "
"is no need to change it.  The name of the remote pseudo tty is returned by "
"the function @code{process-tty-name}."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4092
msgid ""
"If a remote process, started by @code{start-file-process}, should @emph{not} "
"use a pseudo tty, this can be requested by setting @code{process-connection-"
"type} to @code{nil} or @code{pipe}.  There is still a pseudo tty for the "
"started process, but some terminal properties are changed, like suppressing "
"translation of carriage return characters into newline."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4096
msgid ""
"The function @code{make-process} allows controlling this explicitly by using "
"the @code{:connection-type} keyword.  If this keyword is not used, the value "
"of @code{process-connection-type} is applied instead."
msgstr ""

#. type: subsection
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4098
#, no-wrap
msgid "Process properties of asynchronous remote processes"
msgstr "Process properties of asynchronous remote processes"

#. type: cindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4099 ../texi/tramp.texi:4221
#, no-wrap
msgid "Asynchronous remote processes"
msgstr "Asynchronous remote processes"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4104
msgid ""
"When available, @value{tramp} adds process properties to process objects of "
"asynchronous properties.  However, it is not guaranteed that all these "
"properties are set."
msgstr ""

#. type: code{#1}
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4106
#, no-wrap
msgid "remote-tty"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4110
msgid ""
"This is the name of the terminal a @var{process} uses on the remote host, i."
"e., it reads and writes on."
msgstr ""

#. type: code{#1}
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4111
#, no-wrap
msgid "remote-pid"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4115
msgid ""
"The process id of the command executed on the remote host.  This is used "
"when sending signals remotely."
msgstr ""

#. type: code{#1}
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4116
#, no-wrap
msgid "remote-command"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4123
msgid ""
"The remote command which has been invoked via @code{make-process} or "
"@code{start-file-process}, a list of strings (program and its arguments).  "
"This does not show the additional shell sugar @value{tramp} makes around the "
"commands, in order to see this you must inspect @value{tramp} @ref{Traces "
"and Profiles, traces}."
msgstr ""

#. type: findex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4125
#, no-wrap
msgid "list-system-processes"
msgstr ""

#. type: findex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4126
#, no-wrap
msgid "process-attributes"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4131
msgid ""
"The functions @code{list-system-processes} and @code{process-attributes} "
"return information about system processes on the respective remote host.  In "
"order to retrieve this information, they use the command @command{ps}, "
"driven by the following constants:"
msgstr ""

#. type: defvr
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4132
#, no-wrap
msgid "Constant tramp-process-attributes-ps-args"
msgstr ""

#. type: defvr
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4135
msgid ""
"This is a list of arguments (strings) @command{ps} is called with.  The "
"default value is appropriate for GNU/Linux remote hosts."
msgstr ""

#. type: defvr
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4137
#, no-wrap
msgid "Constant tramp-process-attributes-ps-format"
msgstr ""

#. type: defvr
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4143
msgid ""
"This is a list of cons cells @code{(@var{key} . @var{type})} for "
"interpretation of the @command{ps} output.  @var{key} is a key used in the "
"@code{process-attributes} output plus the key @code{pid}, and @var{type} is "
"the respective value returned by @command{ps}.  It can be"
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4146
#, no-wrap
msgid "@bullet{} @code{numberp} @tab --- a number"
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4147
#, no-wrap
msgid "@bullet{} @code{stringp} @tab --- a string without spaces"
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4148
#, no-wrap
msgid "@bullet{} @var{number}"
msgstr ""

#. type: multitable
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4150
msgid "--- a string of @var{number} width, could contain spaces"
msgstr ""

#. type: item
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4150
#, no-wrap
msgid "@bullet{} @code{nil} @tab --- a string until end of line"
msgstr ""

#. type: defvr
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4154
msgid "The default value is appropriate for GNU/Linux remote hosts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4159
msgid ""
"If, for example, @code{tramp-process-attributes-ps-args} is declared as "
"@code{(\"-eww\" \"-o\" \"pid,euid,euser,egid,egroup,comm:40,state\")}, the "
"output of the respective @command{ps} command would look like"
msgstr ""

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4166
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    PID  EUID EUSER     EGID EGROUP   COMMAND                                  S\n"
"      1     0 root         0 root     systemd                                  S\n"
"   1610     0 root         0 root     NFSv4 callback                           S\n"
"   @dots{}\n"
msgstr ""
"    PID  EUID EUSER     EGID EGROUP   COMMAND                                  S\n"
"      1     0 root         0 root     systemd                                  S\n"
"   1610     0 root         0 root     NFSv4 callback                           S\n"
"   @dots{}\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4170
msgid ""
"The corresponding @code{tramp-process-attributes-ps-format} has the value"
msgstr ""

#. type: group
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4175
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"@code{((pid . numberp) (euid . numberp) (user . stringp)\n"
" (egid . numberp) (group . stringp) (comm . 40) (state . stringp))}\n"
msgstr ""
"@code{((pid . numberp) (euid . numberp) (user . stringp)\n"
" (egid . numberp) (group . stringp) (comm . 40) (state . stringp))}\n"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:4178
