#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5639
msgid ""
"For the running session, @value{tramp} disables the external package, and "
"you can continue to work.  If you don't want to see this error while "
"activating @value{tramp}, you can suppress it by the same code as above in "
"your @file{~/.emacs}:"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5650
msgid "How to disable other packages from calling @value{tramp}?"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5655
msgid ""
"There are packages that call @value{tramp} without the user ever entering a "
"remote file name.  Even without applying a remote file syntax, some packages "
"enable @value{tramp} on their own.  How can users disable such features."
msgstr ""

#. type: file{#1}
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5659
msgid "ido.el"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5661
msgid "Disable @value{tramp} file name completion:"
msgstr ""

#. type: lisp
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5664
#, no-wrap
msgid "(customize-set-variable 'ido-enable-tramp-completion nil)\n"
msgstr "(customize-set-variable 'ido-enable-tramp-completion nil)\n"

#. type: file{#1}
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5669
msgid "rlogin.el"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5671
msgid "Disable remote directory tracking mode:"
msgstr ""

#. type: lisp
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5674
#, no-wrap
msgid "(rlogin-directory-tracking-mode -1)\n"
msgstr "(rlogin-directory-tracking-mode -1)\n"

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5680
msgid "How to disable @value{tramp}?"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5685
msgid ""
"To keep Ange FTP as default the remote files access package, set this in "
"@file{.emacs}:"
msgstr ""

#. type: lisp
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5688
#, no-wrap
msgid "(customize-set-variable 'tramp-default-method \"ftp\")\n"
msgstr "(customize-set-variable 'tramp-default-method \"ftp\")\n"

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5691
msgid "If you want to enable Ange FTP's syntax, add the following form:"
msgstr ""

#. type: lisp
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5694
#, no-wrap
msgid "(tramp-change-syntax 'simplified)\n"
msgstr "(tramp-change-syntax 'simplified)\n"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5697
#, no-wrap
msgid "tramp-mode"
msgstr "tramp-mode"

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5701
msgid ""
"To disable both @value{tramp} (and Ange FTP), set @code{tramp-mode} to "
"@code{nil} in @file{.emacs}.  @strong{Note}, that we don't use "
"@code{customize-set-variable}, in order to avoid loading @value{tramp}."
msgstr ""

#. type: lisp
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5704
#, no-wrap
msgid "(setq tramp-mode nil)\n"
msgstr "(setq tramp-mode nil)\n"

#. type: vindex
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5707
#, no-wrap
msgid "tramp-ignored-file-name-regexp"
msgstr "tramp-ignored-file-name-regexp"

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5713
msgid ""
"To deactivate @value{tramp} for some look-alike remote file names, set "
"@code{tramp-ignored-file-name-regexp} to a proper regexp in @file{.emacs}.  "
"@strong{Note}, that we don't use @code{customize-set-variable}, in order to "
"avoid loading @value{tramp}."
msgstr ""

#. type: lisp
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5716
#, no-wrap
msgid "(setq tramp-ignored-file-name-regexp \"\\\\`/ssh:example\\\\.com:\")\n"
msgstr "(setq tramp-ignored-file-name-regexp \"\\\\`/ssh:example\\\\.com:\")\n"

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5720
msgid ""
"This is needed, if you mount for example a virtual file system on your local "
"host's root directory as @file{/ssh:example.com:}."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5724
msgid ""
"To unload @value{tramp}, type @kbd{M-x tramp-unload-tramp @key{RET}}.  "
"Unloading @value{tramp} resets Ange FTP plugins also."
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5729
msgid "What is the difference between Ange FTP and @value{tramp}?"
msgstr ""

#. type: itemize
#: ../texi/tramp.texi:5734
msgid ""
"The difference is that Ange FTP uses @command{ftp} to transfer files between "
"the local and the remote host, whereas @value{tramp} uses a combination of "
"@command{ssh} and @command{scp} or other work-alike programs."
msgstr ""

